1
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:13,400
Mookie could be our daughter.

2
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:16,767
She also has a heart-shaped
birthmark on her thigh.

3
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:20,533
Please help me convince my mom
not to harm Mommy Emma.

4
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:24,067
You'll go with me, and we
will never be separated again!

5
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,333
Where are you bringing Mookie?
Bring her back to us!

6
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,433
I'm not the kidnapper! Ouch!

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,333
Emma!

8
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:31,267
Let's go!

9
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,333
Mommy, what are you doing?

10
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,300
Don't make it difficult
for both of us.

11
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,133
Just go with me.

12
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,867
- Mom!
- You stole Baby Kayla before,

13
00:00:38,933 --> 00:00:40,100
but it will never happen again.

14
00:00:40,167 --> 00:00:42,267
And I won't let you hurt
my child again!

15
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,833
Olive is not a kidnapper.

16
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:46,300
So don't believe those liars.

17
00:00:46,367 --> 00:00:48,700
So, she's my biological mother?

18
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,800
You took me from them!

19
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:52,533
You're so evil!

20
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:54,500
I don't want to see her anymore.

21
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:55,867
Mookie, please!

22
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:32,867
We're now here, dear.
We're here. Don't...

23
00:01:32,933 --> 00:01:35,367
No! Mookie!

24
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:37,000
Mookie, I'm your mother!

25
00:01:37,067 --> 00:01:38,033
Mookie!

26
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:39,167
Mookie, please!

27
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,667
- Let go of my daughter!
- Mookie!

28
00:01:43,733 --> 00:01:46,033
- Mookie, please! Mookie!
- Let her go.

29
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:49,200
- Olive! Stop!
- What are you doing?

30
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:51,033
I said stop!

31
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,767
Her name's Kayla! You witch!

32
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:55,733
And we are her
biological parents.

33
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,800
Uncle Danilo.

34
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:04,733
Call me daddy, dear.

35
00:02:06,067 --> 00:02:07,133
I'm your father.

36
00:02:07,867 --> 00:02:09,333
I'm your father.

37
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,500
Daddy, Dad!

38
00:02:20,267 --> 00:02:22,867
And I'm your grandmother,
my dear grandchild.

39
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,133
Grandma Ligaya.

40
00:02:56,033 --> 00:02:57,867
According to Maricon's
livestream,

41
00:02:57,933 --> 00:03:00,567
Mookie isn't Olive Caparas's
biological child.

42
00:03:00,633 --> 00:03:02,833
Emma Joseco is her mother.

43
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:06,033
What? Is that true?

44
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:12,500
- Oh, no!
- The child might fall!

45
00:03:27,233 --> 00:03:28,833
Is he that man?

46
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,400
Mookie's father?

47
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:32,300
He is Emma's husband?

48
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:34,867
Didn't you run me
over that night?

49
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,500
Because you had an evil motive.

50
00:03:36,567 --> 00:03:38,533
And that was to steal our child!

51
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,633
No! No!

52
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:42,867
They aren't Mookie's parents.

53
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:45,100
They're just confusing you!

54
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:47,200
Mookie is your daughter, Olive.

55
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:50,600
Why can't you say anything?

56
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:52,233
Is it because Danilo's correct?

57
00:03:55,100 --> 00:04:00,767
That means you've always had
something wrong with your head.

58
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,600
You're the crazy ones!

59
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,767
Go to sleep and start dreaming.

60
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,300
Because that's only where
Mookie can be with you!

61
00:04:08,367 --> 00:04:10,467
- Olive! Olive!
- Olive, what are you doing?

62
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:12,267
- Oh, no!
- The kid!

63
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,367
- Poor kid.
- Oh, no! Oh, no!

64
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:15,967
Go ahead and try!

65
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:17,500
Try to steal my child again!

66
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:31,867
Do you see that?

67
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:33,600
Wait, I'll zoom it in.

68
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,000
Stop it!

69
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:36,000
Get out of here!

70
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,567
Mookie!

71
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:42,300
- I said stop!
- Stop!

72
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:44,933
That's enough! Stop it.

73
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,967
You! Stay out of this!

74
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:50,033
We already know the truth!

75
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:51,500
What kind of a friend are you?

76
00:04:51,567 --> 00:04:53,033
Enabler!

77
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,533
I won't let this happen!

78
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,400
- You can't get...
- Hey!

79
00:04:56,467 --> 00:04:57,933
- I said stop!
- Let go of my child!

80
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,867
Wait, I'll zoom in.

81
00:04:58,933 --> 00:05:00,567
- Stop!
- No!

82
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:02,800
You're gonna
hurt my daughter!

83
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:07,300
- Please stop! Let go!
- Mookie! Mookie!

84
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:11,400
- No!
- The kid is hurting. Stop!

85
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:16,733
Mookie!

86
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,233
Mookie!

87
00:05:27,233 --> 00:05:30,133
- Mookie! Mookie!
- Mookie, wake up!

88
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,733
- Mookie, dear, wake up!
- Granddaughter.

89
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,200
- This is my fault!
- Granddaughter.

90
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,967
This is all my fault!

91
00:05:36,033 --> 00:05:37,867
- Astrid, do something!
- Dear, wake up!

92
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:40,067
- Mookie!
- Danilo, the car is downstairs!

93
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:41,900
Let's bring her to the hospital!
The one nearest here!

94
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:43,233
- My car! Let's use my car!
- Okay, okay.

95
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:45,233
- Carry her.
- Hurry up!

96
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,900
Watch her head!

97
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:51,833
Mookie, please!

98
00:05:54,567 --> 00:05:59,267
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

99
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:08,167
- Mookie!
- Get well, dear.

100
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:11,533
- We just got reunited!
- Mookie!

101
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,567
My dear.

102
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:15,800
Mookie. Mookie!

103
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:19,667
- Mookie, get well, dear.
- I will take care of you.

104
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,800
We just reunited.

105
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:23,767
- Mookie!
- Mookie, dear!

106
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:26,667
- Mookie!
- No! Let me in! I'm a doctor!

107
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:29,133
- Please wait over there.
- Mookie!

108
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,133
- Let me in! I'm a doctor!
- Just wait over there!

109
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,533
Let's go. Let's go.

110
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,100
I'm a doctor! My child needs me!

111
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,867
I'm a doctor!

112
00:06:36,933 --> 00:06:39,600
Can you stop?
You're not a real doctor!

113
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:45,033
You better sit
down for now.

114
00:06:45,100 --> 00:06:45,967
Come on.

115
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:10,667
Who are the
patient's parents?

116
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:12,400
- That's me!
- Me.

117
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,800
- Doc...
- Doc, how's my daughter?

118
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:18,667
Has Mookie regained
consciousness?

119
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:21,700
Doc, can we now
see our daughter?

120
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:25,067
Her condition remains
to be very fragile.

121
00:07:25,133 --> 00:07:28,067
Her vital signs
are still unstable.

122
00:07:28,133 --> 00:07:31,633
But, Doc,
is she going to be okay?

123
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,567
Please.

124
00:07:32,633 --> 00:07:35,433
She hit her head hard.

125
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:38,867
And we have conducted
an initial test.

126
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:43,100
But until now,
the patient is in a coma.

127
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,367
We need to closely monitor
her vital signs

128
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:50,967
while we're waiting for the
results of further tests,

129
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:53,900
particularly her CT scan.

130
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:56,800
So we can assess the
extent of damage

131
00:07:56,867 --> 00:08:01,033
and also determine
the best course of action.

132
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,033
Doc.

133
00:08:02,100 --> 00:08:03,333
Doc, please.

134
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,600
Please do everything that
you can to save my daughter.

135
00:08:06,667 --> 00:08:09,833
Please do everything.
Save my daughter.

136
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:12,733
I cannot
provide any guarantees.

137
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:15,033
But we are doing
everything we can.

138
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:16,933
Please excuse me.

139
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:19,500
Doc, please do everything!

140
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:22,467
I'll pay for it
no matter the cost!

141
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:28,900
Something...

142
00:08:29,867 --> 00:08:33,133
that you can't do
for or give Mookie.

143
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,133
So if I were you,

144
00:08:37,533 --> 00:08:38,900
I'd leave.

145
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:45,100
Just ignore her.

146
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:51,333
- Don't listen to her.
- I want to be alone for now.

147
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,900
Emma!

148
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:53,767
Emma!

149
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:55,967
Leave her be.

150
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,167
Dear God.

151
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,500
Did you return Kayla to us
just to get her back again?

152
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,833
What did we do to deserve this?

153
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:23,200
Where did we go wrong?

154
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,433
None of these
would have happened

155
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,867
if you didn't mess
with me and Mookie!

156
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,967
This is all your fault!

157
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:44,733
The nerve of you
to tell me that!

158
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,067
This wouldn't happen to Mookie

159
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:48,267
if you didn't kidnap
and push her!

160
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:52,667
I closed my eyes and endured all
your insults as your laundress.

161
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:54,767
I stayed away from Mookie
like you wanted.

162
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,567
Even though it hurts.

163
00:09:56,633 --> 00:10:02,533
But I'll fight you now that I
know I have more right to her!

164
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:04,767
In your dreams.

165
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:07,700
Leave Mookie and me alone.

166
00:10:07,767 --> 00:10:09,300
You really don't stop.

167
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:10,400
You don't stop being a fake.

168
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:11,900
A fake doctor.

169
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:13,500
And now a fake mother.

170
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:15,000
How dare you!

171
00:10:15,067 --> 00:10:16,833
Which one of us is fake?

172
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:19,067
Which one of us is fake!
Darn you!

173
00:10:19,133 --> 00:10:22,200
Since you're pretending
to be a doctor,

174
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:23,700
why don't you operate
on your brain

175
00:10:23,767 --> 00:10:26,267
so that you'll realize that
Mookie isn't your daughter?

176
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:27,733
How dare you!

177
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:30,200
The nerve of you to touch me!

178
00:10:32,767 --> 00:10:34,133
Show me what you got!

179
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:39,133
- Let go of me!
- You need surgery

180
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,833
on that long horn of yours!

181
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:44,433
Stop it! I will sue you!
You animal!

182
00:10:44,500 --> 00:10:47,867
Go ahead, do what you want.

183
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:50,000
Tell everyone I'm the kidnapper!

184
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,400
But once something happens
to my daughter,

185
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:54,333
I will take your horns off!

186
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:59,567
Oh, boy. Fine.
Let's just leave Emma be.

187
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:00,833
Like she said...

188
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,567
she wanted to be alone.

189
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:05,567
Then let's give her that.

190
00:11:05,633 --> 00:11:08,900
But, Mom, I can't let Emma be
alone.

191
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,833
I know how painful
it is for her

192
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:14,133
to think that our daughter
is in danger.

193
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:17,767
Please excuse me, Mom.

194
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,367
I'll just look for Emma.

195
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:26,267
You kept my daughter
and me apart for years.

196
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:28,767
You kept us from being
together and happy.

197
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:32,200
And now she's fighting
for her life because of you!

198
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:36,933
I took care of Maria Angela!

199
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:44,600
I wish you really did that.

200
00:11:44,667 --> 00:11:45,933
But no.

201
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,733
You experimented on my daughter.

202
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:50,133
You gave her
all kinds of illnesses.

203
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,167
If you really are a parent,

204
00:11:51,233 --> 00:11:54,700
you'll feel how painful
this is for me!

205
00:11:58,600 --> 00:11:59,900
Let go of me!

206
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,133
Monster!

207
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,867
Darn you!

208
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:06,100
- Darn you!
- There they are!

209
00:12:06,167 --> 00:12:07,500
- Emma!
- Olive!

210
00:12:07,567 --> 00:12:09,733
- Stop!
- How dare you!

211
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,600
Darn you! You thick-faced woman!

212
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,900
Leave my wife alone!

213
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,300
You, too!

214
00:12:16,367 --> 00:12:18,933
I'll sue both of you!

215
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,100
I'll make sure
you'll rot in jail!

216
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,833
Let's see who'll rot in jail!

217
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:28,633
- Let's go.
- Darn you!

218
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:32,900
- I said stop! Stop!
- Olive! Stop it!

219
00:12:32,967 --> 00:12:35,133
- Let's go. Let's go!
- I will fight you!

220
00:12:35,967 --> 00:12:38,133
I'm not done with you yet,
you monster!

221
00:12:52,933 --> 00:12:55,067
Our friend
is so deep in thought.

222
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:56,400
You know her.

223
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:57,667
Here we go. Wait.

224
00:13:00,667 --> 00:13:01,633
BFF,

225
00:13:03,033 --> 00:13:04,733
we saw the livestream of...

226
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:05,500
who's that again?

227
00:13:05,567 --> 00:13:08,133
- Maricon.
- Maricon Rivera.

228
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,233
Olive is a monster.

229
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:13,700
I really hope Mookie
wakes up now.

230
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,067
Why did this happen now

231
00:13:17,133 --> 00:13:18,100
that I've learned
she's my granddaughter?

232
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:20,233
She's Baby Kayla.

233
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:22,833
Then this happened.

234
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,000
That's enough, BFF.

235
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:28,067
At least...

236
00:13:29,567 --> 00:13:31,200
the truth has come out.

237
00:13:31,267 --> 00:13:34,400
And Mookie's with you now.

238
00:13:34,467 --> 00:13:35,700
Yeah.

239
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,033
BFF...

240
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:43,833
Let's just pray for Mookie
to get better.

241
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,133
I hope so.

242
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,600
I really hope so.

243
00:13:49,833 --> 00:13:52,867
Hey. Wow.

244
00:13:52,933 --> 00:13:56,467
Maricon's livestream has
already reached 500,000 views.

245
00:13:56,567 --> 00:13:58,400
- Oh!
- About what happened.

246
00:13:58,467 --> 00:13:59,800
- Oh, yeah.
- It has gone viral.

247
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:01,900
- Look.
- Don't be sad anymore.

248
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:03,500
- Cancel it.
- Look.

249
00:14:11,033 --> 00:14:11,700
Dan,

250
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:15,467
I can't bear seeing
Kayla like that.

251
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,467
Mookie.

252
00:14:17,533 --> 00:14:19,233
Do you want to go out?

253
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:22,667
It'll only hurt you
seeing her like that.

254
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,133
Dan, our daughter! Dan!

255
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,600
Doc! Nurse!

256
00:14:31,667 --> 00:14:33,367
Doc! We need your help!

257
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:35,667
- Doc!
- Doc!

258
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:38,167
Administer one dose of epi.
Stat now!

259
00:14:42,533 --> 00:14:45,367
Mookie, dear.

260
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:49,100
Ma'am, please leave
the room for now.

261
00:14:49,167 --> 00:14:50,167
How about my daughter?

262
00:14:50,233 --> 00:14:51,967
- Wait.
- Emma, come on. Let's go out.

263
00:14:52,033 --> 00:14:53,067
It'll only hurt you.

264
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:54,467
- Let's listen to them.
- I want to make sure

265
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:58,467
- my child's safe! Dan! Dan!
- Let's go!

266
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:01,867
- They know what to do.
- Mookie!

267
00:15:03,867 --> 00:15:05,433
- Emma.
- Mookie!

268
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:08,000
Mookie!

269
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:09,233
Mookie, dear!

270
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,367
Wake up!

271
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:15,933
Olive, I've seen the livestream
of the vlogger Maricon Rivera.

272
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,200
It has gone viral!

273
00:15:17,267 --> 00:15:19,900
Everyone already knows
you kidnapped Mookie.

274
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:21,867
Seriously, Astrid?

275
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:26,100
Did Emma and Danilo
already fool you, too?

276
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:27,733
You shouldn't have
made a scene there.

277
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:30,167
You should've just
let Mookie go.

278
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:31,533
There!

279
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,600
That's where you're good at!

280
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:34,800
Blaming!

281
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:38,033
Olive, you kidnapped Mookie.

282
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,767
And if they find solid evidence,

283
00:15:39,833 --> 00:15:41,900
what you did to Danilo
can be revealed.

284
00:15:41,967 --> 00:15:45,667
They can file multiple
charges against you.

285
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:47,333
Shut up.

286
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,567
Shut up!

287
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:51,433
Mookie, dear.

288
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:02,400
Vital signs, stable. Thank God.

289
00:16:06,133 --> 00:16:08,100
What's wrong with you?

290
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:11,133
Why does it seem like
this is all my fault?

291
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,367
What I did to Mookie...

292
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:19,067
I didn't mean to do that.

293
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:21,967
I did that
without thinking.

294
00:16:23,233 --> 00:16:26,500
I'm just scared
to lose my child.

295
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:31,933
We're not even sure if
Maria Angela will survive.

296
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:37,933
They took my daughter.
Why am I the bad guy?

297
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,667
Astrid,

298
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:41,767
I'm the victim here!

299
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:54,367
The doctor's here.

300
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:55,200
Doc.

301
00:16:55,267 --> 00:16:58,300
Doc, how's our daughter?

302
00:16:58,367 --> 00:17:01,233
We have stabilized
her vital signs.

303
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:01,933
However...

304
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:04,667
she's still in a coma.

305
00:17:04,733 --> 00:17:08,300
And we still can't say
when she'll wake up.

306
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:14,233
Doc, please do everything
to save our child.

307
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:19,067
We've just learned that
she's our missing daughter.

308
00:17:19,167 --> 00:17:22,167
We've only spent
a little time with her.

309
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:25,667
We want to have a chance
to be her parents.

310
00:17:26,733 --> 00:17:27,867
We'll do everything.

311
00:17:29,033 --> 00:17:31,000
- Excuse me.
- Thank you.

312
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,433
Dear.

313
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:48,267
Dear, your dad
and I are here.

314
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,200
We've looked for you.

315
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,200
We didn't know
you were just near us.

316
00:17:58,867 --> 00:18:01,133
I wish we found it sooner.

317
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:04,700
I wish we helped you sooner.

318
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:12,333
It's so painful to think
you've endured everything.

319
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:16,533
And we were not there
when you were suffering.

320
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:34,500
Bukoy knows someone
in the police station.

321
00:18:34,567 --> 00:18:37,033
They said Bukoy's testimony
wasn't enough

322
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,800
to file a case against Olive.

323
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:44,933
Does that mean we can't
put Olive in jail yet?

324
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,200
Maybe.

325
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:49,400
And about the child abuse,

326
00:18:49,467 --> 00:18:52,333
they said we need solid evidence

327
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:55,000
to prove that Olive
is mistreating Mookie.

328
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:58,100
And about Olive's kidnapping,

329
00:18:58,167 --> 00:19:04,167
we need proof that we are
Mookie's biological parents.

330
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:07,567
I want Olive to pay
for what she did to us.

331
00:19:07,633 --> 00:19:09,767
But how?

332
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:13,367
And I don't want her
to pay for the hospital bills.

333
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:16,633
Don't worry, Emma.

334
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,300
I'll borrow money
from my employer.

335
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:20,233
He said he'd lend me.

336
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:23,267
And my co-workers
are willing to help.

337
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,867
Kutsy,
and our neighbors.

338
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:26,933
Don't worry.

339
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,167
We'll find solid evidence.

340
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:31,667
There is Emma and Danilo.

341
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,833
- Look at this.
- Mom, what's that?

342
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:37,333
A netizen said
what you should do

343
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:41,067
to prove you are Mookie's
parents.

344
00:19:41,133 --> 00:19:42,933
Right! Correct!

345
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,133
We should heed the
netizen's advice.

346
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:47,400
Yes. Do what they told you to do
step by step.

347
00:19:47,467 --> 00:19:48,400
There's nothing
wrong if we try.

348
00:19:48,467 --> 00:19:49,433
Right?

349
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:52,067
- Let's do what they say.
- Correct!

350
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:53,667
If that is the solution
let's do it.

351
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:56,433
And what they said was clear.
They are fighting...

352
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:57,733
- they said...
- Let's do it. Let's do it.

353
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,133
Olive kidnapped our child!

354
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,733
Our former neighbor, Bukoy, saw
it.

355
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,767
Yes, that's true.

356
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:09,833
I saw Olive take Emma
and Danilo's child.

357
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:10,700
Wow.

358
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:17,400
How much did they bribe
you to accuse me of kidnapping?

359
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,900
They're poorer than a mouse
living in a gutter.

360
00:20:21,967 --> 00:20:23,733
- You are so mean.
- Yuck.

361
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:27,100
Or maybe you're a drunkard.

362
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:31,000
That's why it's enough for you
to have a bottle of...

363
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:33,067
what do you call that?

364
00:20:33,133 --> 00:20:34,633
Four corners?

365
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,633
Cuatro Cantos.

366
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:36,800
Whatever.

367
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:41,567
I'm sure you're in cahoots
with Emma and Danilo

368
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:44,067
to taint my reputation.

369
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,800
Bukoy's telling the truth.

370
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:47,167
Right.

371
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:48,900
So, just admit it.

372
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,100
Go ahead.

373
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:59,233
Show solid proof that
I took your child.

374
00:21:02,267 --> 00:21:04,333
What?

375
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,233
Where's your evidence?

376
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:12,600
That's what I'm talking about.

377
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:16,133
In kidnapping case, substantial
evidence is needed

378
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,767
to prove Miss Caparas'
involvement.

379
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:23,733
We only need one proof.

380
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:26,300
Really, Emma?

381
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:29,667
And what's your brilliant idea?

382
00:21:31,267 --> 00:21:32,633
DNA test.

383
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:35,000
Let's all three of us
have a DNA test.

384
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,500
What?

385
00:21:53,767 --> 00:21:55,067
No!

386
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:57,167
I don't have anything
to prove to you!

387
00:21:58,367 --> 00:22:00,067
I'm Mookie's biological mother.

388
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:02,400
So it's up to me.

389
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:04,533
I have the right to refuse
a DNA test,

390
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:08,533
especially now that the kid's
still in a critical condition.

391
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,200
Why don't you want to do it?

392
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:11,967
Don't you want anyone
to know the truth?

393
00:22:12,033 --> 00:22:14,067
That you kidnapped Mookie?

394
00:22:17,167 --> 00:22:18,200
That's probably the reason

395
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:20,467
why you don't want to take
a DNA test.

396
00:22:34,433 --> 00:22:36,567
In the case of your friend,

397
00:22:36,633 --> 00:22:40,367
she has this delusion
that she genuinely believes

398
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:43,467
that her adopted child
is her biological child.

399
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:46,533
You need to bring her to me,
Astrid.

400
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,733
Before your friend does
something terrible.

401
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,767
You'll be in jail alone.

402
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:54,900
The sadness that is greater than
what I felt

403
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,000
when you stole my child
will kill you.

404
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:58,833
Emma's really getting
on my nerves.

405
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:05,533
It's as if she's sure her DNA
will match with Mookie's.

406
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,367
Olive.

407
00:23:07,867 --> 00:23:09,933
The DNA test results are out.
